Chris Kanich I am an Assistant Professor at the University of Illinois at Chicago in the Department of Computer Science University of Illinois at Chicago Department of Computer Science Contact information  ckanich uic edu              kaytwo kaytwo What I look like I conduct research on the socio technical aspects of cybersecurity  My current nwork includes analysis of gains and losses due to undesirable activity on the nInternet  investigating human factors in effective Internet security nmechanisms  and building new technological primitives with the goal of nincreasing the practical security and privacy of Internet users I am very interested in new collaborations  motivated students  and lively nconversation regarding security research  Our feature usage paper on The Provocateur Podcast  July         nCloudsweeper on Science Friday  July         nShow Me the Money in The Economist  Oct   th      nClick Trajectories in The New York Times  and the editorial  May      nSpamalytics in Wired magazine  March      feature usage paper The Provocateur Podcast Cloudsweeper Science Friday Show Me the Money The Economist Click Trajectories The New York Times editorial Spamalytics Wired magazine Cloudsweeper allows users to audit  encrypt  and redact sensitive information within cloud storage accounts  This project helps us better understand the role of cleartext password emailing  the underground value of stolen accounts  and new ways to improve the security of sensitive  globally accessible information Cloudsweeper The CRISP project is building a new web front end language and paradigm to enable rich document publishing while providing greatly increased privacy and security over traditional HTML JS CSS based sites Our Harm Measurement research effort aims to characterize and quantify the damage experienced by victims of cybercrime Ph D  students  Sara Amini Mohammad Ghasemisharif Mohammad Taha Khan John Kristoff Ph D  alums  Peter Snyder Alums  Sruti Bhagavatula Joshua Casto